The paper is primarily concerned with the quantitative assessment of security in software, which suggests that it may belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Symbolic Execution and SMT solvers, which are commonly used in the areas of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Programming Languages (cs.PL), and Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper introduces a new research problem related to SMT, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
